{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5e5ba064-dbfc-4286-8760-7846ecad8445","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_SwDfVM7koNRWagVamQueVE","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Providing NativeAOT crash dump config"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_GwrtzrQgLrxPFdEcVfEBoW","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cat << 'EOF'\n# Pod spec changes for NativeAOT .NET 11 crash dump collection\nEOF","description":"Display info header","initial_wait":10},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Display info header"}],"interactionId":"ccbd39d5-8363-4e0b-b324-b891de6dcc19","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. I need to provide:\n\n1. The environment variables needed to configure .NET to use createdump for automatic crash dump collection\n2. The Kubernetes pod spec changes needed\n\nFor .NET NativeAOT apps, crash dump collection works differently than regular CoreCLR apps. Let me think about what's needed:\n\nFor .NET (CoreCLR), you typically set:\n- `COMPlus_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` or `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1`\n\n\n- `COMPlus_DbgMiniDumpName` or `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` for the dump path\n- `COMPlus_DbgMiniDumpType` or `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` for dump type\n\nFor NativeAOT, the crash dump support uses different mechanisms since the runtime lacks the same managed debugging infrastructure. Starting with .NET 8, NativeAOT supports crash dumps through environment variables, though the exact configuration differs from CoreCLR.\n\nFor NativeAOT crash dumps, I need to set `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` to enable them, then configure the dump path with `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName`, the dump type with `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` (where 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full), and potentially `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics=1` for diagnostics. The tricky part is that they have a custom createdump tool path, so I need to figure out the right environment variable to point to it—it might be `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpCreatedumpPath` or something similar. For NativeAOT, I need to clarify that the crash handling uses signal handlers built into the runtime itself, and the same `DOTNET_*` environment variables apply, though the mechanism differs from CoreCLR since there's no managed runtime layer to intercept crashes.\n\nFor Kubernetes, I'd need to configure the pod spec with environment variables like `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` to enable crash dump generation, set up a volume mount for storing the dumps, and potentially adjust security context settings to grant ptrace capabilities that createdump requires. I need to specify the createdump path explicitly with `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`, and for Kubernetes deployments, the container requires `SYS_PTRACE` capability, a writable volume for the dumps, and an appropriate core dump size limit configured through the security context. Let me put together the full pod specification with these settings.","outputTokens":1679,"requestId":"C3DB:1BD126:1BDB089:1F79AA8:6A07C26D"},"id":"d4ba34a8-087b-4427-969a-cf284c5a837c","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:04:10.162Z","parentId":"60c04206-acc7-4e62-8603-bf0f88a665f8"}
