{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ee7c341a-6e84-412a-893b-b2ce14f254cd","content":"Here's what you need:\n\n## Environment Variables\n\nFor NativeAOT, set these on your container:\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"                          # Full dump (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t.dmp\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n  - name: DOTNET_EnableCrashReport\n    value: \"1\"                          # Also generates JSON crash report\n```\n\n## Pod Spec Changes\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: my-app\n      # ... your image, ports, etc.\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add:\n            - SYS_PTRACE        # Required: createdump uses ptrace\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi          # Adjust based on expected dump size\n```\n\n## Key points:\n\n| Setting | Why |\n|---------|-----|\n| `SYS_PTRACE` | createdump needs ptrace to read process memory |\n| `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` | Tells NativeAOT runtime where createdump lives (non-default path) |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4` | Full dump — use `2` (Heap) if size is a concern |\n| `emptyDir` volume | Writable location for dumps; swap for a PVC if you need persistence across pod restarts |\n| `DOTNET_EnableCrashReport` | Bonus: writes a `.json` crash report alongside the dump |\n\nFor **production**, consider replacing `emptyDir` with a PersistentVolumeClaim or shipping dumps to blob storage via a sidecar, since `emptyDir` is lost on pod eviction.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ccbd39d5-8363-4e0b-b324-b891de6dcc19","outputTokens":551,"requestId":"C3CF:61C51:1C58159:1FEAF97:6A07C28A"},"id":"4faf856e-a863-44c8-ba74-832c273ca9e9","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:04:20.074Z","parentId":"93eb1c01-bcd2-4f19-80c8-4d49bebf78a4"}
